
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dh_autotools-dev_restoreconfig` baraye bazgardandan file-haye configuration default baraye package-haye autotools-based estefade mishavad. In dastoor be tore otomatick file-haye backup shode ".orig" ya ".rej" ro ke az taraf autotools sakhte shode and, pak mikonad ya bazgardand mikonad. Hadaf az in kar, tamiz negah dashtane source tree az file-haye ezafi dar hengam sakhtan package Debian ast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--name=NAME` --> 🏷️ Esme package binary ra moshakhas mikonad. Agar estefade nashavad, esm az روی Debian package control file khande mishavad.
    🔹 `--sourcedir=DIR` --> 📁 Directory source code ra moshakhas mikonad. Agar estefade nashavad, directory current estefade mishavad.
    🔹 `--no-backups` --> 🚫 File-haye backup shode ".orig" va ".rej" ra bazgardand nemikonad, balkeh anha ra hazf mikonad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dh_autotools-dev_restoreconfig

    🔹 Bazgardandan configuration file-haye default baraye package binary asli.

    $ dh_autotools-dev_restoreconfig --name=foo

    🔹 Bazgardandan configuration file-haye default baraye package binary "foo".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dh_autotools-dev_restoreconfig --no-backups

    🔹 File-haye backup shode ".orig" va ".rej" ra be jaye bazgardandan, hazf mikonad, ta source tree tamiztar bashad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dh_autotools-dev_restoreconfig` command is used to restore default configuration files for autotools-based packages. It automatically removes or reverts backup files (".orig" or ".rej") generated by autotools. This helps keep the source tree clean from unnecessary files during Debian package builds.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--name=NAME` --> 🏷️ Specifies the binary package name. If not used, the name is read from the Debian package control file.
    🔹 `--sourcedir=DIR` --> 📁 Specifies the source code directory. If not used, the current directory is used.
    🔹 `--no-backups` --> 🚫 Instead of reverting backup files (".orig" and ".rej"), it deletes them.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dh_autotools-dev_restoreconfig

    🔹 Restores default configuration files for the main binary package.

    $ dh_autotools-dev_restoreconfig --name=foo

    🔹 Restores default configuration files for the binary package "foo".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dh_autotools-dev_restoreconfig --no-backups

    🔹 Deletes backup files (".orig" and ".rej") instead of reverting them, to keep the source tree cleaner.
